Defendant Edward N Darracott in court, in custody, with attorney Peter M Wolff.   Andrea M. Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 and Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.


Court orders the following: 
Ct. 1:
- Total sentence: 5 years 6 months (Initial Confinement: 18 months - 64 days credit, Extended Supervision: 4 years) consecutive to Ct. 2
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration 
- Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program. 
- Court Costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision 
- Restitution of $137.00 to be paid on the Burglary charge in 15CF350 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision
- Conditions of Extended Supervision: AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. No use or possession of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription. No drug paraphernalia. Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed; Inform Agent of all prescriptions. Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling.  No contact with the victims in case 15CF350.  Absolutely no weapons.  Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided.

Ct. 2:
- Total sentence: 5 years 6 months (Initial Confinement: 18 months, Extended Supervision: 4 years) consecutive to Ct. 1
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration

- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision
